### Usage

This extension allows you to give specific styles to individual pages. To enable this feature, add `script.data` and/or
`style.data` files to a folder that has the same name as the page slug and is stored in the same directory level. Write
custom CSS code in `style.data` file, and custom JS code in `script.data` file.

~~~ .txt
.\
└── lot\
    └── page\
        ├── lorem-ipsum\
        │   ├── script.data
        │   └── style.data
        └── lorem-ipsum.page
~~~

These HTML classes will be added to the root element if it has a `class` attribute when the current page has custom CSS
and/or custom JS data. You can use this feature to create a specific look or response on your site from the client-side
when the following classes are found in the root element:

`is:art`
: Will be added if custom CSS or JS data of current page isn’t empty.

`not:art`
: Will be added if custom CSS and JS data of current page are empty.

Example usage in CSS code:

~~~ .css
.not\:art a {
  color: #00f;
}
~~~

Example usage in JS code:

~~~ .js
if (document.documentElement.classList.contains('is:art')) {
    console.info('This page contains custom CSS/JS code.');
}
~~~

These additional conditional statements are available for use in layouts to show/hide elements on your site from the
server-side:

`$site->is('art')`
: Returns `true` if current page has custom CSS or JS.

`$site->not('art')`
: Returns `true` if current page doesn’t have custom CSS and JS.

Example usage in HTML/PHP code:

~~~ .html.php
<?php if ($site->is('art')): ?>
  <p>
    <?= i('This page contains custom CSS/JS code.'); ?>
  </p>
<?php endif; ?>
~~~